## Favorite Existing Apps - Categorize and Evaluate
### Instagram
   - **Category:** Photo & Video / Social 
   - **Mobile:** Website is view only, uses camera, mobile first experience.
   - **Story:** Allows users to share their lives in pictures and enhance their content with filters
   - **Market:** Anyone that takes pictures could enjoy this app. Ability to follow and hashtag based on interests and categories allows users with unique interests to engage with relevant content.
   - **Habit:** Users can post throughout the day many times. Features like "Stories" encourage more candid posting as well. Users can explore endless pictures in any category imaginable whenever they want. Very habbit forming!
   - **Scope:** Instagram started out extremely narrow focused, just posting pics and viewing feeds. Has expanded to a somewhat larger scope including "Instagram Stories" (a la SnapChat) and messenger features. 
   
## New App Ideas - List
1. Todo list with calendar
   - At todo list with a built in calendar. First tab allows overview of work. Create new assignments and assign deadlines. 
2. Playlist Organizer 
    - Organize playlists on music apps according to vibe, tempo, artist, or genre. 
3. Budgeting App
    - An application that allows you to input your current income, balance, and savings to plan your finances based on need and want costs. 
4. Chatroom/Messaging App
    - Messaging app that allows for interaction between up to 5 users.
5. Study Motivation App
    - An app that gamifies studying. For example, you clock in when studying and gain points for the amount of time you log. Bonus points for completing tasks you set a to do list for. The points earned can be used to buy accessories for the main screen. Maybe a pet or bed room or smthn?
6. Career Choice? App
    - An app that takes what studies or interests, career wise, and personal interests to help choose the perfect career for the the user. Provide tips or requirements for certain jobs(good for high school students probably)
7. Personality Quizzes App
    - Small entertainment app that works like Buzzfeed Quizzes. Maybe can have a customized quiz for users to make and share with friends. 
8. Journaling App*
    - Daily use app that provides prompts for journaling, a section for mood tracking, and a streak feature that keeps users engaged and coming back daily. 
9. Music Reviewing App
    - This is an app similar to Letterboxd where you can review music instead of movies and tv. You can provide track by track rankings, add your favorite albums to your profile, and see what other users are reviewing. 
10. Exerciser: Walking Game App
    - This app is an entertainment mobile game simliar to PokemonGo. The user must around their neighborhood and parks to banish ghosts and ghouls. It's a fun way to help users get their steps for the day.

## Top 3 New App Ideas 
1. Music Reviewing App
2. Study Movitavtion App/Todo List Combo
3. Exerciser: Walking Game App

## New App Ideas - Evaluate and Categorize
1. Study Movitation App (with Todo List and Calendar)
   - **Description**: Allows students to track their current assignments. Will include a weekly assignments tab, calendar that shows when assignments are due, and a study streak features that rewards students with good studying habits. 
   - **Category:** Productivity
   - **Mobile:** This app will include a calendar feature to log when assignments are due. A study timer/time logging feature. Points systems/rewards for completing study goals, and integration with school assignment apps, i.e. Canvas. 
   - **Story:** This app aims to push productive students closer to their studying and academic goals. Using this app will improve your overall academic health. 
   - **Market:** Students that are looking to improve their study habits or track their academic progress. 
   - **Habit:** Due to the studying streak feature, students will want to return to this app daily to keep up with their points and continue to customize their study rooms. 
   - **Scope:** V1 would allow for calendar and assignment tracking functions to be used. V2 would introduct the study timer/study tracking goals. V3 would add a way for students to earn and obtain rewards for goals met. V4 expand the scope of student rewards when redeeming points.

2. Music Reviewing App
    - **Description:** Allows users to do music reviews, curate playlists, and create profiles to share their favorite albums and tracks. You can also view other profiles. 
    - **Category:** Social Networking and Entertainment 
    - **Mobile:** Uses multiple screens. Allows users to upload photos for their app review covers. Allows social media esque connectivity. 
    - **Story:** Allows users to show their personalities and individuality through their music taste. 
    - **Market:** Music lovers who want to showcase their opinions. Could also be used by artists to promote their new projects through advertising. 
    - **Habit:** Users will want to update their profile with any new music they have recently discovered or new artist drops. 
    - **Scope:** V1 would allow users to review music from 0-5 stars by creating profiles. V2 will allow users to curate playlists. V3 will add social networking with other profiles.
    
3. Exerciser(Walking Game App)
    - **Description:** Exerciser is a mobile app game that is meant to promotes health and entertainment. The user is to walk around their areas to defeat enemies in the app and earn rewards, allowing for a friendly and heroic environment for those who wish to improve their physical health while enjoying their time doing so.
    - **Category:** Health and Entertainment. 
    - **Mobile:** uses mobile location to track the position of users device and to asist in step count tracking. 
    - **Story:** Allows user to play a game while they are working on their physical health.
    - **Market:** Users looking for a chance to add light excerise of walking to their day while also wanting something to bring entertainment on that walk. 
    - **Habit:** Users can use the app at anytime. After defeating enemies of the game users are rewarded in-game currency, that can be spent on in-game rewards. Users can create and edit their profile. 
    - **Scope:** V1 would allow the user icon to move around on a map based off of their devices phyical location. V2 would allow profile customisation and randomised battle locations that are activated when the users device location is near the battle , as well as a in-app steps counter. V3 would allow rewards and coins for the user after battles(implimentation of in-game currency) and a small in-game store to spend coins, and a health tip section to assist users on their technics. V4 would have a timer for break reminds so users don't overwork themselves. (other customisation additions or social additions possibly but not focused)

